=== w-mnt3t5h8-943e2a2ef85f ===
{
  "id": "w-mnt3t5h8-943e2a2ef85f",
  "type": "quest",
  "status": "open",
  "title": "Astrolabe efficiency: reader/full-inventory cost reduction",
  "body": "<!-- Live body for this quest is a file in the vibers guild. See .claude/skills/quests/SKILL.md. -->\n<!-- Do not edit this row body while the quest is live. -->\n\n## Goal\n\nCut Astrolabe's end-to-end latency and token cost substantially, with the initial focus on the reader stage and its full-repository inventory pass — currently suspected to be the dominant contributor. The outcome is (a) a profile of where Astrolabe's time and tokens actually go across its stages, (b) a chosen set of interventions on the reader/inventory path (scoping, caching, incremental re-reads, hierarchical summarization, or similar), and (c) a sketch of any cross-stage changes that follow from the profiling (e.g., handoff format changes, dropping work the reader does that downstream stages don't use).",
  "createdAt": "2026-04-10T16:12:01.916Z",
  "updatedAt": "2026-04-13T21:36:06.960Z",
  "links": {
    "outbound": [],
    "inbound": []
  },
  "parent": null,
  "children": {
    "summary": {
      "open": 1
    },
    "items": [
      {
        "id": "w-mnyx6ajh-ae9d4622cf36",
        "title": "GSD-intel-style atlas for Astrolabe reader",
        "status": "open"
      }
    ]
  }
}
=== w-mnyx6ajh-ae9d4622cf36 ===
{
  "id": "w-mnyx6ajh-ae9d4622cf36",
  "type": "quest",
  "status": "open",
  "title": "GSD-intel-style atlas for Astrolabe reader",
  "body": "<!-- Live body for this quest is a file in the vibers guild. See .claude/skills/quests/SKILL.md. -->\n<!-- Do not edit this row body while the quest is live. -->\n\n## Goal\n\nPort the GSD `/gsd-intel` pattern into Astrolabe: maintain a queryable project-shape artifact (structural + interpretive intel) that downstream planning stages consume instead of re-scanning the codebase from scratch on every commission. Outcome is (a) an intel schema tailored to what Astrolabe's reader/analyst/spec-writer actually need, (b) a build/refresh mechanism split between cheap non-LLM tooling (structural) and a one-time LLM mapper pass (interpretive), with freshness tracking, and (c) a reader/MRA prompt shape that consumes the intel as preamble or as MCP-tool-backed queries — turning the reader from a 25-turn exploration into a single-shot or near-single-shot pass over prepared context.",
  "parentId": "w-mnt3t5h8-943e2a2ef85f",
  "createdAt": "2026-04-14T17:52:54.749Z",
