=== w-mnz8kj86-141e5b12bf7c ===
{
  "id": "w-mnz8kj86-141e5b12bf7c",
  "type": "quest",
  "status": "open",
  "title": "Atlas layer 1: prose preamble generated by LLM mapper",
  "body": "<!-- Live body for this quest is a file in the vibers guild. See .claude/skills/quests/SKILL.md. -->\n<!-- Do not edit this row body while the quest is live. -->\n\n## Goal\n\nDesign and ship the first layer of the Astrolabe atlas: a set of prose markdown documents produced by an LLM mapper rig and injected as preamble into Astrolabe's planning stages, selected per commission by a brief-type → document-subset map. This is the \"turn-killer\" layer that directly addresses the SSR failure mode (single-shot without prep doesn't work; single-shot *with* prebuilt interpretive context does). Outcome is (a) a settled document set (which of GSD's seven templates port, what we add), (b) a brief-type → subset map Astrolabe uses to pick 2–3 docs per commission, (c) a mapper rig template that produces the documents, and (d) the reader/MRA prompt changes that consume them.",
  "parentId": "w-mnyx6ajh-ae9d4622cf36",
  "createdAt": "2026-04-14T23:11:54.966Z",
  "updatedAt": "2026-04-14T23:11:54.966Z",
